The face of someone who is trying their best not to let anxiety ruin their life✌🏻 

A lot of things trigger to make it worse but a full moon, a period, asthma & the stress of life has just left me feeling a bit too overwhelmed. I just think it’s important to be honest & vulnerable on here because I promise you no one’s life is as glam as it looks on instagram! 

If you need to rest or a full day in bed then that is okay, those who also suffer with anxiety know that the healing is not linear & sometimes no matter how hard we try an attack will just appear out of nowhere and knock you for six. You’re not a freak, it’s not your fault💖

For the longest time I’ve got so angry at myself saying things like “why can’t I just be normal” “why do the most simple things set me off”. But this is normal for someone who’s an anxiety sufferer and beating ourselves up about is only going to make it worse.

Some things I’ve found helpful when you’re body is in high anxiety mode (deffo need to take my own advice here) 
- eating proper meals & eating healthy where you can
- Trying to leave the house once a day even if it’s for a short walk to the shops 
- Staying off social media or your phone & only watching light hearted comfort shows
- TALKING to your support system or telling a healthcare professional how you’re feeling 
- Obviously staying hydrated and avoiding triggers like caffeine, smoking or alcohol 
- Sleeping and resting properly, if you need to cancel everything and take a full days rest then do it. Nothing is worth ruining your mental health 
- Easy wellness activities that calm your soul like reading, yoga or meditation 
- Long baths or showers 

If you feel yourself having a panic attack:
- drink water
- Sit down, sometimes I put my face in my hands and close my eyes 
- Breathe in for 4 through your nose and out for 4 with your mouth 
- Use your senses, look for things you can see, hear, feel, smell or taste
- Repeat a mantra in your head like “this will pass” or “this isn’t real”

And always remember your current success rate for getting over anxiety to this point has been 100% so be kinder to yourself & know that you will get through this too💖

Stop hiding your body or depriving yourself of joy & waiting until you look ‘just right’… 💜 

TW DISORDERED EATING:
In my experience even when you get to your desired weight you still don’t feel good you just want to lose more, it’s a never ending cycle! I got to a size 6 with extreme dieting & still thought I was fat & kept saying ‘just a little bit more’. I didn’t go to dinner with friends & the thought of going to a birthday gave me anxiety as I knew I’d be expected to eat cake. I was scared to get into a bikini & never believed ex partners when they called me beautiful. What I’m trying to say is there’s nothing wrong with you it’s just your mindset!💜 We deserve to live beautiful lives no matter what weight we are so stop waiting until you like how you look before you start living it. Life really is too short!!!

Being sober is literally just unlocking new parts of your personality everyday that you pushed down & tried to hide with drinking…🙃 

I’ve realised that I am an introvert. I am a little shy & awkward & that is totally okay! I was using alcohol to fake confidence, dance to music I didn’t like & go to places & be around people I didn’t enjoy. It’s so scary finally meeting the real you underneath but it’s also a really beautiful experience💖 When I get on with someone on a deeper level I now know it’s a real bond. When I have a good night out dancing with my friends I feel the real joy from it & don’t forget it in the morning because I’ve blacked out. And I don’t force myself to be in situations I don’t enjoy which caused me to get anxiety… which means I have time to do the things I actually enjoy, like writing, reading, playing games or dance/yoga. It’s so hard for it to not feel like a loss when you lose who you thought you were by being sober but we need to see it as a gain!

Most importantly I’m learning to accept the real me for her flaws. It’s okay to like your own space & be quieter than other people & if your social battery drains faster. I always saw extroverts being rewarded for being fun, popular & outgoing and I wanted a peace of it but forcing myself to be something I’m not with alcohol was just recipe for disaster😅

It doesn’t matter what your life looks like to other people!!! Go at your own pace, follow your gut instinct & create your own path💖 So many people didn’t find their success until their late twenties, thirties, fifties or even sixties. You still have time. Don’t burn yourself out & hate yourself for not being where you thought you’d be by now. There is so much beauty to be found in those moments where we feel lost… usually it means we’re on the edge of a break through🙌🏻✨

Taking a step back doesn’t have to mean backwards, sometimes you just need to change things up so you can enter the next chapter! A year ago I would’ve died if someone said I’d be moving back into my childhood home😅 I saw it as the ultimate failure. But actually a week in I feel so mentally at peace, I’m saving money, can focus on my studies & be closer to my lovely family and friends. It actually has improved my life in so many ways but my ego and the fear of being judged kept me stuck in London for way longer than I needed to be.
